quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  2,275,"Those who devour usury cannot stand{1}except as does one who is being beaten by Satan into insanity. That is because they said, “Trade and usury are certainly the same.” But Allah has permitted trade and has forbidden usury. Thus, to whomsoever an admonition came from his Lord, so he refrained<i class=""s"">(from usury) </i>—then his past earnings belong to him and his matter rests with Allah. Yet whoever reverts—then those{2}are the fellows of the Fire; therein they abide.",footnotes:1:On the Day of Resurrection.|2:A grammatical shift from singular to plural.
  2,276,"Allah eliminates usury and He makes donations grow, for Allah does not love every sinning relentless denier."
  2,277,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds and have established the prayer and have brought{1}the purifying charity{2}—their reward is with their Lord, and <span class=""h"">no fear</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a><span class=""h"">shall be</span>upon them nor shall they grieve.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  2,278,"O you who have attained faith, be mindful of Allah and leave aside what has remained of usury, if you are believers."
  2,279,"But if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>do not, then <span class=""h"">be informed<sup foot_note=""79742"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of a war from Allah and His Messenger. Yet if you repent, then your capitals belong to you—<i class=""s"">(thus) </i>you do no injustice, and you are not done injustice."
  2,280,"But if he{1}has hardship, then deferment until a time of ease. But to donate{2}it is better for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, if you only knew.",footnotes:1:The debtor.|2:To waive it as charity.
  2,281,"And be mindful of a day{1}when <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">are returned<sup foot_note=""79746"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>to Allah, then the earnings of every single self are rendered in full to it, for they{3}are not done injustice.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘guard yourselves against a day’.|3:A grammatical shift from 2nd person to 3rd person.
